<h2 class="text-4xl font-extrabold dark:text-white">Svelte vs SvelteKit</h2>
<p class="font-normal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400 leading-tight">Svelte is a component-based framework that simplifies the process of building interactive and reactive user interfaces by shifting the heavy lifting of DOM manipulation from runtime to compile time, leading to faster and more efficient web applications.</p>
<br />
<p class="font-normal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400 leading-tight">SvelteKit extends Svelte's capabilities by adding file-based routing, server-side rendering, layouts, global stores, and adapters. These features simplify the development workflow, enhance performance, and enable efficient management of global state, making it a powerful choice for building complex, production-ready web applications.</p>
<p><em>via: ChatGPT 3.5</em></p>
